Unbiblical movies. One move starts out with a closeup of a woman's cleavage and curses by taking God's name in vain. Verses are randomly quoted throughout these movies, but Biblical salvation is not introduced. Unequally yoked relationships are encouraged.

In God's country, the woman turns her life around without God. Decision, while not 100% Biblical by far, at least based a movie around the morals instead of trying to throw morals into an already written movie.

These were all good movies, a lot better than I expected. They had such different plots than I am used to seeing. I love that they  are christian oriented.
We can learn something profitable from them.

Spiritual warmth radiates through these films. Each film stresses a different Christian message. The film I enjoyed the most was God's Country. The main character is transformed so completely when she finds a true purpose in life. The change from the most sickening materialistic character to a woman who totally gets  the purpose of life.
Decision was a heart wrenching which shows what can happen when someone is completely down on their luck due to tragedy.
Lukewarm is also well done as it depicts when a young adult fighting his past tries hard to move forward into his future.

I liked all three movies. They were all inspirational in showing how God works in everyone's life. They were not afraid to say God Or Jesus in the movies or to pray and give God the glory. Each movie has it trials and victories. Great family Christian entertainment.
Great movies and they help build your faith in God.
